dPreferences` as specified in design-spec.md. It lazily creates instances via ge
tter instead of constructor injection.\n3. **契约一致性**: ✅ No shared types ch
anges needed.\n4. **测试覆盖**: ⚠️ Missing BDD step definitions for `dev_tools_dr
awer.feature`. Cubit/widget/golden tests are present.\n5. **文档同步**: ✅ All r
equired docs updated/created.\n6. **可运行性**: ✅ `make check-docs`, `make desi
gn-check`, `make agent-check` pass. `make lint`/`make test` can\'t run due to mi
ssing tooling in environment.\n7. **UI/设计一致性**: \n   - ✅ Design assets exi
st\n   - ⚠️ Minor inconsistency between mockup.html and design-spec.md on label/t
itle font sizes, but code follows design-spec.md\n   - ✅ Colors, spacing, dimen
sions match spec\n   - ✅ Widgetbook use cases registered\n   - ✅ Golden files 
included\n\nWait, let me reconsider the "前端变更审查硬规则":\n1. 设计资产存在性
检查: `designs/issue-29/` exists and has `design-spec.md` ✅\n2. 设计一致性检查:
The code generally matches the design-spec.md\n\nOne more thing I noticed: The `
DevToolsRepositoryImpl` has a potential issue. In the design-spec, it shows:\n``
`dart\nclass DevToolsRepositoryImpl implements DevToolsRepository {\n  DevToolsR
epositoryImpl(this._prefs);\n  final SharedPreferences _prefs;\n```\n\nBut the a
ctual code doesn\'t have a constructor parameter for SharedPreferences. The DI r
egistration in `di.dart` uses `DevToolsRepositoryImpl.new`, which works because 
the actual class has a default constructor (implicitly, since no constructor is 
declared). But this doesn\'t match the design-spec and is inconsistent with how 
other repositories are set up (they use `Dio? dio` optional parameters for testa
bility).\n\nActually, looking at `auth_repository_impl.dart`:\n```dart\nclass Au
thRepositoryImpl implements AuthRepository {\n  final Dio _dio;\n  AuthRepositor
yImpl({Dio? dio}) : _dio = dio ?? getIt<DioClient>().dio;\n```\n\nAnd `profile_r
epository_impl.dart`:\n```dart\nclass ProfileRepositoryImpl implements ProfileRe
pository {\n  final Dio _dio;\n  ProfileRepositoryImpl({Dio? dio}) : _dio = dio 
?? getIt<DioClient>().dio;\n```\n\nThe `DevToolsRepositoryImpl` should similarly
accept `SharedPreferences? prefs` for testability and consistency. This is a val
id concern.\n\nAlso, I should check the pubspec.yaml change. The only change is 
adding `shared_preferences: ^2.3.2`. That\'s correct.\n\nLet me also think about
whether `make lint` failure is significant. The failure is because `eslint` is n
ot installed (no node_modules), not because of any code lint errors. This is an 
environment limitation, not a code issue. Similarly, `flutter` not being availab
le prevents running mobile tests. I should note this in the report.\n\nOne more 
check: The auth and profile repository changes. The PR changed them to use `getI
t<DioClient>().dio` instead of `DioClient().dio`. This is because `DioClient` is
now registered as a singleton in DI. But wait - this PR also adds `DioClient` to
DI. The previous code created a new `DioClient()` every time. Now it\'s a single
ton. This is a good change, but if `AuthRepositoryImpl` was previously getting i
ts own `DioClient` instance and now shares one, this is a semantic change. Howev
er, since `DioClient` is stateful (it now has `updateBaseUrl`), making it a sing
leton is necessary for the dev tools to update the base URL for all repositories
. This is architecturally correct.\n\nLet me write the final report now.',
